('953', '1', 'Bring water to a boil under a metal or bamboo steamer. Sprinkle sea bass with salt, black pepper, and cayenne. place on a piece of parchment paper inside steamer. Top with ginger and shiitakes, cover and steam 15 minutes.'),
('953', '2', 'Remove fish and place on a plate. Sprinkle cilantro and green onions on fish. drizzle with juices from parchment. In a small saut pan, heat oil over medium heat for 1 to 2 minutes or until smoking.'),
('953', '3', 'Pour some oil over each fillet to wilt cilantro and green onions.'),
('953', '4', 'Drizzle plates with soy sauce.Bring water to a boil under a metal or bamboo steamer. Sprinkle sea bass with salt, black pepper, and cayenne. place on a piece of parchment paper inside steamer. Top with ginger and shiitakes, cover and steam 15 minutes.'),
('953', '5', 'Remove fish and place on a plate. Sprinkle cilantro and green onions on fish. drizzle with juices from parchment. In a small saut pan, heat oil over medium heat for 1 to 2 minutes or until smoking.'),
('953', '6', 'Pour some oil over each fillet to wilt cilantro and green onions.'),
('953', '7', 'Drizzle plates with soy sauce.'),
('1769', '1', 'Heat 2 tablespoons oil in a 12-inch heavy skillet over moderately high heat until hot but not smoking, then saute onion, stirring frequently, until golden, about 6 minutes. Stir in water and 1/4 teaspoon pepper and cook, stirring, until onion is softened, about 1 minute. Stir in butter until melted, then stir in capers and lemon juice.'),
('1769', '2', 'Remove from heat and keep warm, covered.'),
('1769', '3', 'Preheat broiler.'),
('1769', '4', 'Pat fish dry, then brush all over with remaining tablespoon oil and sprinkle with salt and remaining 1/4 teaspoon pepper. Put fillets, skin sides down, on rack of a broiler pan and broil about 5 inches from heat until just cooked through, 6 to 8 minutes.'),
('1769', '5', 'Serve fish topped with onion mixture and sprinkled with parsley.'),
('1770', '1', 'Mix first 5 ingredients in processor until well blended but still slightly chunky, occasionally scraping down sides of bowl. Season butter mixture to taste with salt and pepper.'),
('1770', '2', 'Transfer to small bowl. DO AHEAD Olive-mustard butter can be prepared 2 days ahead. Cover and refrigerate. Soften slightly at room temperature before using.Preheat oven to 400F.'),
('1770', '3', 'Brush large rimmed baking sheet with olive oil. Arrange salmon fillets on prepared sheet. sprinkle with salt and pepper. Roast salmon just until opaque in center, about 14 minutes.Meanwhile, cook orzo in large pot of boiling salted water until tender but still firm to bite.'),
('1770', '4', 'Drain. return orzo to same pot.'),
('1770', '5', 'Add half of olive-mustard butter and toss to coat. Divide orzo among 8 plates. Top each serving with 1 salmon fillet.'),
('1770', '6', 'Place small dollop of olive-mustard butter atop each salmon fillet.'),
('1770', '7', 'Garnish with whole olives and parsley sprigs, if desired, and serve.'),
('1771', '1', 'Preheat oven to 450F and coat inside of a 13- by 9-inch glass or ceramic baking or gratin dish with 1 tablespoon butter.'),
('1771', '2', 'Cut 2 thin slices from each lemon half and squeeze juice from remaining lemon.'),
('1771', '3', 'Mash together remaining 2 tablespoons butter, 1 teaspoon lemon juice, and shallot and season well with salt and pepper. Sprinkle dish with remaining juice.'),
('1771', '4', 'Cook lettuce in a large pot of salted boiling water 1 minute. Immediately transfer with tongs to a bowl of ice water to cool.'),
('1771', '5', 'Drain lettuce and cut out ribs, leaving top 1 inch of leaves intact.'),
('1771', '6', 'Spread out 1 lettuce leaf lengthwise on a work surface.'),
('1771', '7', 'Place another leaf on first leaf, overlapping enough to cover any holes (use 2 extra leaves if necessary). Season 1 piece halibut with salt and pepper and place crosswise in center of lettuce.'),
('1771', '8', 'Spread top of fish with one fourth of shallot butter. Wrap lettuce over fish to form a packet (dont worry if ends arent covered by lettuce) and transfer to baking dish. Make 3 more packets in same manner, arranging them close together in baking dish.'),
('1771', '9', 'Top each packet with a lemon slice. Cover packets with a sheet of wax or parchment paper, then tightly cover dish with foil.'),
('1771', '10', 'Bake in middle of oven until centers of packets are just firm to the touch, 15 to 20 minutes, depending on thickness of fish.'),
('1771', '11', 'Serve with pan juices poured over packets.'),
('1772', '1', 'Boil asparagus until barely tender-crisp, 2 minutes. drain and rinse asparagus in cold water.'),
('1772', '2', 'Heat grill to medium-high (about 450).'),
('1772', '3', 'Cook leek in butter in a large frying pan over medium heat until soft, 5 minutes.'),
('1772', '4', 'Add thyme, 1/2 tsp. salt, 1/4 tsp. pepper, and the morels. cook, stirring occasionally, until morels are tender, 5 minutes. Stir in sherry and reduce by half, 30 to 45 seconds. Set vegetables aside.'),
('1772', '5', 'Fold a 12- by 17-in. sheet of heavy-duty foil in half crosswise. With a knife tip, poke dime-size holes through foil about 2 in. apart. Oil one side of foil. Rub fish on both sides with oil and put skin side down on foil. Sprinkle with remaining 1/4 tsp. each salt and pepper.'),
('1772', '6', 'Set salmon on foil on cooking grate. grill, covered, until fish is barely cooked through, about 10 minutes. With 2 wide spatulas, slide fish from skin to a warm baking sheet. tent with foil. If you want crisp skin, continue to cook skin on foil until crisp, 1 to 3 minutes more.'),
('1772', '7', 'Remove foil from grill, then gently peel off skin, using fingers or a wide spatula (skin may break into pieces). Set salmon skin, if using, on a platter.'),
('1772', '8', 'Add cream and asparagus to mushrooms and bring to a boil over high heat, stirring. boil longer to thicken sauce if you like. With 2 spatulas, set fish on skin. Spoon half the vegetable sauce over salmon and serve the rest on the side.'),
('1772', '9', 'Serve immediately.'),
('1772', '10', '*Soak dried morels in hot water until softened, 8 minutes. Squeeze out water. cut in half.'),
('1773', '1', 'Preheat oven to 450 degrees.'),
('1773', '2', 'Place salmon on a rimmed baking sheet. season with salt. Roast until opaque throughout, about 15 minutes.'),
('1774', '1', 'Preheat broiler. Melt 4 tablespoons of the butter in a large skillet over medium-high heat.'),
('1774', '2', 'Add the shallot and cook 1 to 2 minutes or until just starting to brown. Sprinkle the flour over the shallot and butter and whisk until smooth. Reduce heat to medium.'),
('1774', '3', 'Add the half-and-half slowly, whisking into a smooth sauce. Cook 2 to 3 minutes, until thickened, whisking as needed.'),
('1774', '4', 'Add the sugar and stir, then add the spinach, nutmeg, salt, and pepper. Cook, stirring occasionally, until hot. Reduce heat to low, so the spinach stays warm.'),
('1774', '5', 'Place the fillets on a broiler pan that has been coated with cooking spray.'),
('1774', '6', 'Pour the lemon juice over the fillets, then sprinkle the bread crumbs evenly on top. Dot with the remaining butter. Broil 5 to 6 minutes or until the fillets are opaque and the bread crumbs golden. Spoon some creamed spinach onto each of 4 plates, then place a fillet on top.'),
('1774', '7', 'Serve with the lemon wedges.'),
('1778', '1', 'Mix first 5 ingredients in  a medium bowl until well combined. Season with salt. DO AHEAD: Can be made 3 days ahead. Cover and chill.Preheat oven to 32'),
('1778', '2', 'Pour  4 Tbsp. oil in a roasting pan just large enough to fit the salmon. Make a bed  of herbs in bottom of pan. top with salmon, skin side down.'),
('1778', '3', 'Drizzle salmon with remaining 2 Tbsp. oil and season with salt. Top with tomatoes, if using.'),
('1778', '4', 'Bake until salmon is just cooked through in the center (a small knife will slide easily through flesh), 2530 minutes. Toss tomatoes with 3 Tbsp. oil, parsley, and za''atar, if using, in a medium bowl. Season to taste with salt. Set aside.Bring a medium pot of lightly salted water to a boil.'),
('1778', '5', 'Add couscous and cook until tender, about 7 minutes.'),
('1778', '6', 'Drain couscous. transfer to a large bowl. Stir in butter and remaining 1 Tbsp. oil. Season to taste with salt. Gently fold tomatoes into couscous'),
('1778', '7', 'Use a large spoon or fork to serve salmon, leaving skin in pan.'),
('1778', '8', 'Serve with yogurt sauce and couscous.'),
('1779', '1', 'On a plate, mix together the paprika, cayenne, thyme, chili powder, garlic powder, cumin, salt and pepper for the blackened spice mixture. Dredge the catfish fillets in the spice mixture and set aside.'),
('1779', '2', 'Heat a large cast iron fry pan or saute pan over high heat until it is "white hot".'),
('1779', '3', 'Add oil to pan. When oil begins to slightly smoke, add catfish fillets and cook on each side, about 2 to 3 minutes. Cook in batches, if necessary, and transfer cooked fillets to a preheated 200 degree F oven while cooking remaining fillets.'),
('1779', '4', 'To serve, top each fillet with 1/2 tablespoon of butter and serve with lemon wedges.'),
('1780', '1', 'Squeeze juice from remaining 2 oranges into small saucepan. place pan over medium-high heat, and bring juice to a boil.'),
('1780', '2', 'Add butter, and stir until melted. remove pan from heat.'),
('1780', '3', 'Brush salmon with orange-juice mixture.'),
('1780', '4', 'Place roasting pan in oven, and roast salmon, basting every 10 minutes with orange-juice mixture, until skin is crispy and dark golden brown and meat is pink and firm to the touch, about 1 hour. If head or tail of fish become too dark, gently fold aluminum foil over them.'),
('1780', '5', 'Remove pan from oven. pour wine into pan to help loosen salmon. Using cheesecloth to help lift fish, carefully transfer to serving platter. Gently remove cheesecloth from under fish, and serve.'),
('1781', '1', 'Preheat the oven to 35'),
('1781', '2', 'In a large ovenproof skillet, heat the oil until shimmering.'),
('1781', '3', 'Add the salmon skin side down and season with salt and pepper. Cook over high heat until the skin is lightly browned, about 3 minutes.'),
('1781', '4', 'Transfer the skillet to the oven and roast the salmon for about 10 minutes, until it is cooked through and the skin is very crisp.'),
('1781', '5', 'Meanwhile, in a large skillet, melt 2 tablespoons of the butter.'),
('1781', '6', 'Add the mushrooms and cook over high heat, stirring occasionally, until lightly browned, about 6 minutes.'),
('1781', '7', 'Add the shallot, garlic and thyme and season with salt and pepper. Cook, stirring, until the shallot is softened, about 3 minutes.'),
('1781', '8', 'Add the wine and broth and simmer until the liquid is nearly evaporated, about 5 minutes.'),
('1781', '9', 'Remove from the heat. Stir in the remaining 2 tablespoons of butter.'),
('1781', '10', 'Transfer the salmon to plates, skin side up.'),
('1781', '11', 'Serve with the mushrooms.'),
('1782', '1', 'Combine first 6 ingredients. Preheat alder plank* in 400 oven.'),
('1782', '2', 'Place salmon, skin side down, on plank. cover with butter mixture.'),
('1782', '3', 'Bake 10 to 15 minutes or until done.'),
('1782', '4', '*We recommend a reusable alder plank with a trough cut in the center to hold juices. (See page 231 for a source.) If using a flat disposable alder plank, place in a shallow baking pan to collect drippings.'),
('1786', '1', 'Prepare grill or broiler.'),
('1786', '2', 'To prepare basil butter, combine first 5 ingredients in a food processor. process until smooth, scraping sides as needed. Set aside.'),
('1786', '3', 'To prepare sauce, heat oil in a saucepan over medium-high heat.'),
('1786', '4', 'Add onion and 2 garlic cloves. saut 3 minutes.'),
('1786', '5', 'Add tomatoes. saut 2 minutes. Stir in wine, capers, vinegar, and sugar. bring to a boil. Reduce heat. simmer 5 minutes, stirring occasionally. Stir in parsley. Set aside.'),
('1786', '6', 'To prepare tuna, sprinkle tuna with 1/2 teaspoon salt and pepper.'),
('1786', '7', 'Place tuna on grill rack or broiler pan coated with cooking spray. Cook 5 minutes on each side or until desired degree of doneness.'),
('1786', '8', 'Serve with sauce and basil butter.'),
('1786', '9', 'Garnish with basil leaves, if desired.'),
('1790', '1', 'Preheat oven to 450F. Stir 2 tablespoons mustard and 1 tablespoon melted butter in small dish. Oil small rimmed baking sheet and place salmon on sheet, skin side down. Sprinkle salmon with salt.'),
('1790', '2', 'Spread top of salmon with mustard mixture and season generously with pepper.'),
('1790', '3', 'Bake until salmon is cooked through and mustard browns, about 10 minutes.'),
('1790', '4', 'Meanwhile, heat remaining 1 tablespoon butter in heavy small skillet over medium heat.'),
('1790', '5', 'Add shallots and saute 2 minutes.'),
('1790', '6', 'Add preserves and vinegar. stir until preserves melt and mixture is smooth. Bring to simmer. Season sauce to taste with salt and pepper.'),
('1790', '7', 'Spoon sauce over fish and serve.'),
('1792', '1', 'Watch how to make this recipe.'),
('1792', '2', 'Preheat grill to medium-high heat.'),
('1792', '3', 'Using aluminum foil, create an oblong cooking tray (approximately 13 inches by 8 inches by 2 inches) to be placed directly on grill.'),
('1792', '4', 'Place salmon fillet in center of tray. Season first with garlic salt, sprinkle with brown sugar, and then cover with pieces of butter. Top with sliced red onions.'),
('1792', '5', 'Pour beer of choice into tray to just below the highest point of the fillet. Cover tray with aluminum foil to envelope fish completely.'),
('1792', '6', 'Place tray on grill, cover with lid, and grill for approximately 8 minutes or until just cooked through.'),
('1793', '1', 'In a large, deep skillet, melt the butter in 2 tablespoons of the olive oil.'),
('1793', '2', 'Add the onion, artichoke hearts, shiitake caps, carrots and garlic and cook over moderately high heat, stirring occasionally, until lightly browned, 7 minutes.'),
('1793', '3', 'Add the chickpeas and stock, season with salt and pepper and bring to a boil. Simmer over low heat until the vegetables are tender and the liquid is nearly evaporated, 5 minutes. Stir in the parsley and chives and keep warm.'),
('1793', '4', 'In a large nonstick skillet, heat the remaining 2 tablespoons of olive oil until almost smoking. Season the cod fillets with salt and pepper, add to the skillet and cook over high heat until well browned on the bottom, about 6 minutes. Carefully flip the fillets and cook until they''re white throughout, about 3 minutes longer.'),
('1793', '5', 'Spoon the vegetables into shallow bowls and top with the seared cod fillets.'),
('1793', '6', 'Serve with lemon wedges.'),
('1794', '1', 'Combine first 3 ingredients. Dredge catfish fillets in cornmeal mixture. place fillets, skin sides down, on a greased baking sheet.'),
('1794', '2', 'Combine Cajun seasoning and seasoned salt. sprinkle over fillets.'),
('1794', '3', 'Drizzle with butter.'),
('1794', '4', 'Bake at 400 for 30 minutes or until golden and fish flakes with a fork.'),
('1794', '5', 'Garnish, if desired.'),
('1796', '1', 'Rinse salt cod well under cool running water.'),
('1796', '2', 'Place in a 1 1/2- to 2-quart jar and cover with water. cover jar airtight and chill 1 to 2 days (see notes), draining and replacing water at least six times.'),
('1796', '3', 'Drain fish. In a 1 1/2- to 2-quart pan, cover salt cod with water. bring to a boil, reduce heat, and simmer until fish flakes easily, 5 to 15 minutes.'),
('1796', '4', 'Drain. when cool enough to handle, remove and discard any bones and skin.'),
('1796', '5', 'Meanwhile, in a 10-inch frying pan or 5- to 6-quart pan over high heat, frequently stir onion and thyme in 2 tablespoons butter until onion is browned, 6 to 10 minutes.'),
('1796', '6', 'Scrape into a bowl.'),
('1796', '7', 'Add broth and potatoes to pan. bring to a boil over high heat, reduce heat, cover, and simmer gently until potatoes mash easily when pressed, 10 to 15 minutes.'),
('1796', '8', 'Drain potatoes.'),
('1796', '9', 'In a food processor (at least 1 qt.) or bowl, combine fish, onion mixture, potatoes, cream, mustard, and pepper. Whirl or beat with a mixer until potatoes are mashed. season to taste with salt.'),
('1796', '10', 'In a buttered shallow 1-quart casserole or four buttered 1-cup ramekins, spread cod mixture level (equally in ramekins) with a spatula, then swirl the top with the tip of the spatula.'),
('1796', '11', 'Break about 1 tablespoon butter into tiny pieces and dot cod mixture evenly, lodging pieces in the crevices.'),
('1796', '12', 'Bake in a 400. oven until golden brown, 20 to 25 minutes. Sprinkle with capers and parsley.'),
('1796', '13', 'Serve hot.'),
('1798', '1', 'If fish fillets are large, cut into serving pieces.'),
('1798', '2', 'Mix butter and lemon juice.In another bowl, mix flour, salt and white pepper.Dip fish into butter mixture. coat fish with flour mixture.'),
('1798', '3', 'Place fish in ungreased square baking dish, 8x8x2 inches.'),
('1798', '4', 'Pour remaining butter mixture over fish. sprinkle with paprika.Cook uncovered in 350 degree oven until fish flakes easily with fork, 25-30 minutes.'),
('1798', '5', 'Garnish with parsley sprigs and lemon slices if desired.'),
('1799', '1', 'Make the rice: bring the stock or water to a boil over high heat. Stir in the rice, butter, and salt. Cover tightly and remove to the lowest possible heat. Cook for 20 minutes.'),
('1799', '2', 'Remove from the heat. Allow to sit for 5 minutes.Meanwhile, in a large skillet, heat 2 tablespoons of olive oil.'),
('1799', '3', 'Saute the onion over medium-high heat until soft, about 5 minutes.'),
('1799', '4', 'Add the zucchini and continue to saut until beginning to soften, about 3 minutes. Stir in the tomatoes, cumin, paprika, and chili powder. Saut over medium heat, stirring occasionally, until the tomatoes have released their juices, about 7 minutes.Fluff the rice with a fork and transfer to the pan with the tomato mixture. Stir to combine. Off the heat, add the lemon juice and cilantro. Taste for seasoning.Make the slaw: combine all ingredients in a medium-mixing bowl. Toss until incorporated. Taste for seasoning and add more salt as necessary.Make the fish: Arrange the catfish fillets in a shallow bowl or baking dish.'),
('1799', '5', 'Pour the buttermilk over the fish. Marinate for 10 minutes.Coat a cast iron skillet with a generous layer of olive oil over high heat.'),
('1799', '6', 'Place the cornmeal on a plate and season with salt and pepper.'),
('1799', '7', 'Remove the catfish from the buttermilk and dredge it in the cornmeal on both sides, shaking off any excess. When the pan is smoking, add the catfish fillets. Fry on both sides until golden brown and very crisp, about 3 minutes per side.'),
('1799', '8', 'Remove to a plate lined with paper towels. When the catfish is cool enough to touch, cut each fillet into two pieces.To serve, place two cups of rice on each plate and top with two pieces of catfish. Using a slotted spoon and leaving as much juice as possible in the mixing bowl, scoop about  cup of slaw on top of the fish.'),
('1799', '9', 'Garnish with fresh chopped parsley and some additional sliced radishes. Enjoy immediately!'),
('1800', '1', 'Preheat oven to 400F.'),
('1800', '2', 'Mix butter, garlic powder, Italian seasoning and ground mustard in medium bowl until well blended.'),
('1800', '3', 'Place fish on foil-lined shallow baking pan. Sprinkle with salt and pepper.'),
('1800', '4', 'Spread fish with herb butter mixture.'),
('1800', '5', 'Bake 10 minutes or until fish flakes easily with a fork.'),
('1801', '1', 'Heat the oven to 180C.'),
('1801', '2', 'Place the fish fillets in a shallow ovenproof dish with the bay leaves and pepeprcorns. Almost cover with milk and cook for 10 minutes until just cooked and the fish can be flaked. Discard the milk, pepeprcorns and bay leaves.'),
('1801', '3', 'Remove the skin and gently flake the fish, discarding the bones together with the skin.Warm a large pot over gentle heat and melt the butter.'),
('1801', '4', 'Add the onion, thyme and celery to the pot and cook gently for about 20 minutes until soft. Wash the diced potatoes until the water runs clear, drain and add to the pot with the leeks and 850ml water. Simmer for 45-60 minutes.'),
('1801', '5', 'Pour the cream into the soup and, when bubbling, add the flaked fish.'),
('1801', '6', 'Remove from the heat immediately, garnish with chives and serve with crusty bread.The first picture in this post is my submission to the Snackshots event created and hosted by my friend Michelle at the Greedy Gourmet. The theme for the month is leeks and the deadline is today! So get leek-snapping'),
('1801', '7', 'More deliciousness for you!Caldo verde soup'),
('1801', '8', 'Pan-fried salmon on kale, sweet potato and pomegranate'),
('1801', '9', 'Smoked haddock with flageolets in a creamy mustard sauce (or Nigel Slater does WTSIM)Leek & potato soup: creamy-dreamy & easy-peasy'),
('1805', '1', 'Watch how to make this recipe.'),
('1805', '2', 'For the swordfish: Stir together 8 cups water, the salt, sugar and peppercorns in a deep pot. Bring to a boil just to dissolve the salt and sugar. cool completely. Submerge the swordfish in the brine. Refrigerate for 12 hours.'),
('1805', '3', 'Remove the swordfish from the brine and rinse well under cold water. Pat dry and allow to air dry for at least 1 hour. The exterior of the fish should feel sticky to the touch before smoking.'),
('1805', '4', 'Prepare a smoker with maplewood chips and to an internal temperature of 200 to 225 degrees F.'),
('1805', '5', 'Brush the fish very lightly with canola oil and sprinkle with salt and pepper. Smoke the fish for about 2 hours, adding chips through the first hour as necessary. You can keep adding chips the second hour if you prefer a much smokier flavor.'),
('1805', '6', 'Transfer the smoked fish to a large platter.'),
('1809', '1', 'Preheat oven to 375 degrees. In a large skillet, heat remaining 2 tablespoons oil over high heat. Pat fish dry with paper towels and season both sides with salt and pepper.'),
('1809', '2', 'Place in skillet and cook until browned on both sides.'),
('1813', '1', 'Remove the skin from the smoked haddock and place the fish in a lightly buttered baking dish.'),
('1813', '2', 'Pour over the milk, then add enough water almost to cover the fish. Tuck in a couple of bay leaves and grind over some black pepper.'),
('1813', '3', 'Bake at 200C for about fifteen to twenty minutes or until you can pull one of the large, fat flakes of flesh out with ease.'),
('1813', '4', 'Drain and discard the milk.Rinse and re-butter the baking dish, making sure you remove any bits of skin from the milk left behind. Rinse the beans in a sieve under running water, then empty them into a mixing bowl.'),
('1813', '5', 'Pour in the cream and a couple of tablespoons of milk, then chop the parsley and add it together with the mustard, a grinding of black pepper and a little salt. Go easy on the salt as the smoked fish is already pretty salty.Spoon the beans into the dish and lay the fish on top, spooning some of the creamy beans over the top to keep it moist. Turn the oven down to 180C and bake for about forty minutes, until the cream is bubbling and the sauce has thickened around the beans.Nigel serves his his with steamed spinach, and I admit that it is a lovely combination, but steamed green beans as pictured above work just as well.This post is my entry for this months Waiter, Theres Something in My event where the theme was pulses, hosted by ME! I am slowly working my way through all your entries and hope to have the round-up posted later this week.More deliciousness for you!Pan-fried salmon on kale, sweet potato and pomegranate'),
('1813', '6', 'Leek and smoked haddock chowder'),
('1813', '7', 'Smoked salmon pat moulds'),
('1813', '8', 'Baked rolled gurnard with a mustard cream sauce'),
('1814', '1', 'Mix wine, butter, Old Bay and tarragon in small bowl.'),
('1814', '2', 'Brush on both sides of fish fillets.Grill or broil fish 8 to 10 minutes per inch of thickness or until fish flakes easily with a fork. Turn once during cooking and brush again with sauce. Discard leftover sauce.'),
('1815', '1', 'Cover lentils with cold water by 1 1/2 inches in a 2-quart saucepan and bring to a boil. Simmer, uncovered, until lentils are just tender, 12 to 25 minutes.'),
('1815', '2', 'Drain in a sieve set over a bowl and reserve 1/2 cup cooking liquid.'),
('1815', '3', 'While lentils are simmering, melt butter in a 2- to 3-quart heavy saucepan over moderately low heat, then stir in onion, garlic, and salt and cook, covered, stirring occasionally, until pale golden, about 10 minutes.'),
('1815', '4', 'Remove lid and cook, uncovered, stirring occasionally, until golden, 5 to 10 minutes more.'),
('1815', '5', 'Stir in lentils and enough reserved cooking liquid to moisten (1/4 to 1/2 cup) and cook until heated through.'),
('1815', '6', 'Just before serving, stir in parsley, lemon juice, pepper, and 1 tablespoon oil.'),
('1818', '1', 'Melt one tablespoon clarified butter in a skillet over medium heat.  As the clarified butter melts, season the trout filets with one-half teaspoon unrefined sea salt and one teaspoon ground black pepper.'),
('1818', '2', 'Places the trout skin-side down in the melted butter and cook, covered, for about eight minutes or until the fish flakes easily when pierced by a fork.  Keep warm while you prepare the chanterelles.Melt remaining tablespoon clarified butter in a separate skillet over medium heat.  Stir in minced shallot and fry until fragrant and translucent, about two minutes.  Stir in sliced chanterelles and fry three to five minutes or until softened slightly.'),
('1818', '3', 'Pour in heavy cream and cook, stirring constantly, until the cream is thick and glossy  about two minutes.  Stir in parsley and serve over trout.'),
('1819', '1', 'Preheat oven to 400 degrees F.'),
('1819', '2', 'In a small bowl, combine the Italian seasoning, black pepper, paprika, salt, and cayenne. Season each piece of fish with the rub.'),
('1819', '3', 'Heat a large skillet over medium-high heat and add the butter and oil. Once the butter has melted, add the fish and cook about 2 minutes per side.'),
('1819', '4', 'Transfer the whole pan to the oven and cook for another 4 to 6 minutes.'),
('1820', '1', 'In a small saucepan over high heat, bring mango nectar and mango to a boil. As mango begins to break down, press down on it with a fork or potato masher, to mash it. Continue cooking until mango cooks down to form a chunky puree, about 15 minutes.'),
('1820', '2', 'Remove half to serve as a sauce. Set the other half aside for dredging.'),
('1820', '3', 'On a large plate, mix together flour, cornmeal, sugar and salt.'),
('1820', '4', 'Preheat a large skillet.'),
('1820', '5', 'Season salmon with salt and freshly ground black pepper.'),
('1820', '6', 'Brush glaze over top of salmon, then dredge in cornmeal mixture.'),
('1820', '7', 'Add oil and butter to skillet. Over high heat, sear salmon cornmeal mixture face down until golden, about 6 to 8 minutes for medium rare, flipping halfway through to crisp skin.'),
('1821', '1', 'Drain the liquid from the tuna cans. If you are using tuna packed in water, reserve a tablespoon of the tuna water, and add a teaspoon of olive oil to the tuna mixture in the next step.2'),
('1821', '2', 'Mix tuna with mustard, bread, zest, lemon juice, water, parsley, chives, hot sauce, salt, pepper, egg:In a medium bowl, mix together the tuna, mustard, torn white bread, lemon zest, lemon juice, water, parsley, chives, and hot sauce. Sprinkle on salt and freshly ground black pepper. Taste the mixture before adding the egg to see if it needs more seasoning to your taste.'),
('1821', '3', 'Mix in the egg.3 Form into patties, chill:Divide the mixture into 4 parts. With each part, form into a ball and then flatten into a patty.'),
('1823', '1', 'Preheat the broiler. Lightly season the salmon fillets with salt and pepper. Wrap 3 slices of the bacon crosswise around each salmon fillet, spacing the slices 1 inch apart.'),
('1823', '2', 'Place the salmon fillets in a medium roasting pan and broil the fish 6 inches from the heat for about 13 minutes, shifting the pan halfway through, or until the salmon fillets are just cooked through.'),
('1823', '3', 'Meanwhile, in a large skillet, cook the bacon pieces over high heat, stirring occasionally, until lightly browned and slightly crisp, about 4 minutes.'),
('1823', '4', 'Pour off all but 2 teaspoons of the bacon fat and reduce the heat to moderately high.'),
('1823', '5', 'Add the mushrooms to the skillet and saut them until they are golden brown, about 3 minutes. Reduce the heat to moderate and stir in the chopped parsley, 2 tablespoons of the chopped chives and the minced garlic. Cook until the garlic is fragrant, about 1 minute.'),
('1823', '6', 'In a small bowl, whisk the hot water with the oyster sauce until blended.'),
('1823', '7', 'Add to the mushrooms and cook over moderately high heat, stirring, until the sauce thickens slightly, about 1 minute. Stir in the nutmeg, then whisk in the butter and cook until just melted.'),
('1823', '8', 'Remove the mushroom sauce from the heat.'),
('1823', '9', 'Remove the strips of bacon from the salmon fillets and cut each fillet into 3 pieces. Save the broiled bacon slices for another use.'),
('1823', '10', 'Transfer the salmon to a large platter. Spoon the mushroom sauce over the fish, garnish with the remaining 2 tablespoons of chopped chives and serve immediately.'),
('1825', '1', 'Heat oven to 400 F. Cook the rice according to the package directions. Meanwhile, in a shallow bowl, combine the paprika, cayenne, thyme, garlic powder, and 1/2 teaspoon of the salt. In a saucepan, over medium heat, melt 2 1/2 tablespoons of the butter and add the lemon juice.'),
('1825', '2', 'Heat a large ovenproof skillet over medium-high heat. Working with 1 salmon fillet at a time, dip the top and bottom first in the lemon butter, then in the spices. Cook the salmon until blackened, 2 minutes per side.'),
('1825', '3', 'Transfer to oven for 8 minutes. Stir the corn, parsley, and the remaining salt and butter into the rice.'),
('1825', '4', 'Transfer the salmon and rice to individual plates and serve with the lemon wedges.'),
('1826', '1', 'Combine first 4 ingredients in a shallow dish.'),
('1826', '2', 'Place potato flakes in another shallow dish. Dip fillets in buttermilk mixture. dredge in potato flakes. Melt butter in a large nonstick skillet over medium-high heat.'),
('1826', '3', 'Add fish. cook 3 minutes on each side or until golden and fish flakes easily when tested with a fork.'),
('1826', '4', 'Serve with lemon wedges.'),
('1827', '1', 'Clean and skin the eel, and then cut it into chunks. In a large bowl, mix together 1 cup flour, seasonings, oil, garlic, onion, and pepper.'),
('1827', '2', 'Add the eel to this mixture and then marinate in the refrigerator for 1 hour.'),
('1827', '3', 'Dredge the marinated eel in flour. In a saute pan over medium heat, sear the eel until golden brown, about 7 minutes.'),
('1827', '4', 'Add the white wine and cook until reduced by half.'),
('1827', '5', 'Add the butter and cook until it melts and browns slightly. Divide the eel among 4 serving plates and top with the butter sauce.'),
('1829', '1', 'Preheat the oven broiler. Grease a baking dish.'),
('1829', '2', 'In a bowl, mix the Parmesan cheese, butter, mayonnaise, lemon juice, green onions, salt, and hot pepper sauce.'),
('1829', '3', 'Arrange the halibut fillets in the prepared baking dish.'),
('1829', '4', 'Broil halibut fillets 8 minutes in the prepared oven, or until easily flaked with a fork.'),
('1829', '5', 'Spread with the Parmesan cheese mixture, and continue broiling 2 minutes, or until topping is bubbly and lightly browned.'),
('1830', '1', 'Blend together eggs, water, flour, and salt in a blender until smooth.'),
('1830', '2', 'Transfer to a bowl and stir in tarragon.'),
('1830', '3', 'Lightly brush a 10-inch nonstick skillet with melted butter and heat over moderate heat until hot but not smoking. Ladle about 1/4 cup batter into skillet, tilting and rotating skillet to coat bottom, then pour excess batter back into bowl. (If batter sets before skillet is coated, reduce heat slightly for next crespella.) Cook until just set and underside is lightly browned, about 30 seconds, then invert crespella onto a clean kitchen towel in one layer to cool. (It will be cooked on one side only.) Make 5 more crespelle with remaining batter in same manner, brushing skillet with butter as needed and transferring to towel as cooked, arranging them in one layer.'),
('1831', '1', 'Watch how to make this recipe.'),
('1831', '2', 'Preheat the oven to 425 degrees F.'),
('1832', '1', 'Special equipment: 4 heart-shaped pieces parchment paper'),
('1832', '2', 'Preheat the oven to 350 degrees F.'),
('1832', '3', 'Spray the bottom of the parchment paper with nonstick spray. Season the salmon with salt and pepper and place on the right side of the paper.'),
('1832', '4', 'Combine the julienne vegetables and toss together. Season with salt, pepper, and 2 tablespoons soy sauce.'),
('1832', '5', 'Place an even amount of black beans and julienne vegetables on top of each fillet. Top with 2 slices of the chilled butter.'),
('1832', '6', 'Drizzle some white wine and soy sauce over and around fish. Sprinkle with ginger.'),
('1832', '7', 'Starting with the "point" of the paper heart, roll and crimp the edges until the fillets are totally encased and sealed in the "half-heart" shape.'),
('1832', '8', 'Place packages on a cookie sheet.'),
('1832', '9', 'Place pan in the center of the oven without a rack above it.'),
('1832', '10', 'Bake for 15 to 20 minutes, until the parchment has puffed and is light brown.'),
('1832', '11', 'Remove from oven and transfer to oval platters for serving.'),
('1832', '12', 'In a glass bowl, combine all ingredients for the butter.'),
('1832', '13', 'Mix well.'),
('1832', '14', 'Place butter on a piece of plastic wrap and roll the plastic to form into a 1/2-inch thick cylinder. Refrigerate the butter to set up, about 15 to 20 minutes.'),
('1833', '1', 'To make the stuffing, in a small saucepan over high heat, combine the stock and lemon juice and bring to a boil.'),
('1833', '2', 'Add the rice, reduce the heat to low, cover and cook until the rice is tender and the liquid has been absorbed, about 18 minutes.'),
('1833', '3', 'Remove from the heat and let stand, covered, for 5 minutes.Meanwhile, in a fry pan over medium-low heat, melt the butter.'),
('1833', '4', 'Add the leek and saut, stirring frequently, until soft, about 5 minutes.'),
('1833', '5', 'Remove from the heat.When the rice is ready, add it to the leek mixture and mix well.'),
('1833', '6', 'Let cool to room temperature. Stir in the parsley, chives, tarragon and lemon zest, and season with salt and pepper.Preheat an oven to 400F. Generously oil the bottom of a shallow roasting pan just large enough to hold the salmon.Run your fingers lightly over the surface of the fish to locate any pin bones and remove them with tweezers or small needle-nosed pliers. Rinse the fish and pat dry with paper towels. Season the cavity with salt and pepper. Spoon the rice mixture into the cavity, taking care not to pack it too tightly. Tie 3 pieces of kitchen twine around the width of the fish, spacing them evenly, to secure the stuffing in place.'),
('1833', '7', 'Brush or rub the skin with olive oil.'),
('1833', '8', 'Cut the onion into slices 1/2 inch thick. Thinly slice the lemon. Arrange the onion and lemon slices in the prepared pan.'),
('1833', '9', 'Place the salmon on the onion-lemon bed, scatter the tarragon around the fish and pour the wine into the bottom of the pan.Roast the salmon, basting 1 or 2 times with the pan juices, until an instant-read thermometer inserted into the thickest part of the fish, away from the backbone, registers 140F, or the fish flakes when a knife is inserted into the thickest part, 50 to 60 minutes.'),
('1833', '10', 'Transfer the salmon to a large platter and tent with aluminum foil.'),
('1833', '11', 'Let rest for 15 minutes.To serve, remove the strings.'),
('1833', '12', 'Cut the salmon into slices 1 inch wide and transfer to warmed individual plates.'),
('1833', '13', 'Serves 6 to 8.Adapted from Williams-Sonoma, Essentials of Roasting, by Rick Rodgers, Melanie Barnard & Bob & Colleen Simmons (Oxmoor House, 2004).'),
('1835', '1', 'In a small bowl, mix together paprika, dry mustard, cayenne pepper, cumin, black pepper, white pepper, thyme and salt. set aside.'),
('1835', '2', 'Heat a heavy cast iron pan on high heat until extremely hot, about 10 minutes.'),
('1835', '3', 'Pour 3/4 cup melted butter into a shallow dish. Dip each fillet into butter, turning once to coat both sides. Sprinkle both sides of fillets with spice mixture, and gently pat mixture onto fish.'),
('1835', '4', 'Place fillets into hot pan without crowding. Carefully pour about 1 teaspoon melted butter over each fillet. Cook until fish has a charred appearance, about 2 minutes. Turn fillets, spoon 1 teaspoon melted butter over each, and cook until charred. Repeat with remaining fish.'),
('1840', '1', 'Preheat oven to 500 degrees F (260 degrees C).'),
('1840', '2', 'In a small bowl, combine the milk and salt.  In a separate bowl, mix together the bread crumbs, Parmesan cheese, and thyme.  Dip the haddock fillets in the milk, then press into the crumb mixture to coat.'),
('1840', '3', 'Place haddock fillets in a glass baking dish, and drizzle with melted butter.'),
('1840', '4', 'Bake on the top rack of the preheated oven until the fish flakes easily, about 15 minutes.'),
('1841', '1', 'Preheat grill for medium-high heat.'),
('1841', '2', 'Place butter, brown sugar, garlic, lemon juice, soy sauce, and pepper in a small saucepan. Warm over medium heat, stirring occasionally, until sugar is completely dissolved.'),
('1841', '3', 'Lightly oil grill grate.'),
('1841', '4', 'Brush fish with brown sugar sauce, and place on grill. Cook for 5 minutes per side, or until fish can be easily flaked with a fork, basting with sauce. Discard remaining basting sauce.'),
('1843', '1', 'To make the stuffing: Melt butter or margarine in a large saucepan over a medium-low heat.'),
('1843', '2', 'Saute onion, celery, and parsley until all of the vegetables are just tender.'),
('1843', '3', 'Mix in crabmeat, shrimp, and vermouth. Season with salt, pepper and hot pepper sauce. cook until shrimp is finished cooking (it will be pink).'),
('1843', '4', 'Mix in bread crumbs, a little at a time. When the mixture holds together well, stop adding bread crumbs. Taste and add more seasoning (salt, pepper, and hot pepper sauce) if necessary. Set this mixture aside to let it cool.'),
('1843', '5', 'Spray a baking sheet with non-stick cooking spray.'),
('1843', '6', 'Roll 1 sheet of puff pastry onto a flat surface. The puff pastry, once rolled should be about 1/3 to 1/4 inch thick and large enough for you to lay the fish on top of it and still have puff pastry on the sides. Lay one of the fish fillets on top of the puff pastry.'),
('1843', '7', 'Spread the stuffing mixture evenly over the fish fillet.'),
('1843', '8', 'Place the remaining fillet over the stuffing. Trim the pastry around the filets in roughly the shape of a fish. Save the trimmings.'),
('1843', '9', 'Roll second sheet of puff pastry out to about 1/3 to 1/4 inch thick.  Drape second sheet over stuffed fillets, making sure that there is enough of the top sheet to tuck under the bottom sheet of puff pastry.  Trim the top sheet of pastry about 1/2 inch larger than the bottom sheet.'),
('1843', '10', 'Brush underside of top pastry sheet with water and tuck under bottom sheet of puff pastry pressing lightly to totally encase the fish and stuffing package.'),
('1843', '11', 'Place the sealed packet on the prepared baking sheet, and let it cool for 10 to 15 minutes.'),
('1843', '12', 'While packet is chilling, roll out pastry scraps.  From the scraps cut out fins, an eye and ''lips''.  Attach cut-outs to chilled package with a little water.  Use an inverted teaspoon to make indentations in puff pastry to resemble fish scales but do not puncture pastry.  Chill entire package.'),
('1843', '13', 'While the package is chilling, preheat the oven to 425 degrees F (220 degrees C).'),
('1843', '14', 'Remove the fish from the refrigerator and brush the package with the egg yolks. Measure the thickness of the package at its thickest part.'),
('1843', '15', 'Bake for 15 minutes, then reduce the temperature to 350 degrees F (175 degrees C) and bake the fish for 10 extra minutes per inch of measured thickness. Test for doneness by inserting a thermometer into the package, when the temperature reaches 140 degrees F (70 degrees C) the fish is finished cooking.'),
('1844', '1', 'In a bowl, stir together vegetable oil, orange juice, 3 tablespoons lime juice, tequila, 1 tablespoon lime zest, 1 tablespoon habanero pepper, and garlic. Reserve a small amount to use as a basting sauce, and pour the remainder into a shallow baking dish.'),
('1844', '2', 'Place the salmon in the shallow dish, and turn to coat. Cover, and refrigerate for 2 to 4 hours, turning frequently.'),
('1844', '3', 'In a small bowl, mix together softened butter, garlic salt, 1 tablespoon lime juice, 2 teaspoons habanero pepper, and 2 teaspoons lime zest. Cover, and refrigerate.');